VIRAL GASTROENTERITIS, ROTAVIRUS - EL SALVADOR
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 19 Jan 2012
Source: SDPnoticias.com, Notimex report [in Spanish, trans. Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ, edited]
http://sdpnoticias.com/nota/282338/Aumentan_consultas_por_diarrea_y_rotavius_en_El_Salvador


The Ministry of Health of El Salvador reported an increase in gastrointestinal diseases and rotavirus [infections] in the 1st week of January 2012, totaling 11 521 cases.

According to a report provided by the health minister, Maria Isabel Rodriguez, during the 1st week of January 2012 there were 4112 more consultations for diarrhea than those registered during the same period in 2011.

In addition, the official confirmed that of 109 samples tested for rotavirus in the 1st week of January 2012, 51 were positive.

Rodriguez attributed the increase in consultations for diarrhea or gastroenteritis to Salvadorans drinking contaminated water, the lack of hand washing, and the dry season.

Regarding rotavirus [infection], manifested through vomiting and diarrhea, the official explained that 5 year old children are most vulnerable to becoming infected with the disease.

Rodriguez called on parents to comply with preventive measures issued by the Ministry of Health to protect their children from rotavirus infection and gastrointestinal diseases.

